      "My favourite weekend of the year!"<br />
    </p>
    <a href="#one" class="more scrolly">Learn More</a>
  </section>

  <!-- One -->
  <section id="one" class="wrapper style1 special">
    <div class="inner">
      <header class="major">
        <h2>
          The sixth Velotour Festival will take place over two weekends (same
          itinerary) in 2026<br />
        </h2>
        <p>
          100 cycling enthusiasts will gather to make a 3-day bicycle tour in
          Belgium, share their excitement about slow travel and have a great
          time together. You can choose between two long weekends (same
          itinerary): from 15 to 17 May and from 23 to 25 May 2026. The festival
          is organised by Welcome To My Garden and its community.
        </p>
      </header>
      <!--
							<ul class="icons major">
								<li><span class="icon fa-bell major style1"><span class="label">Lorem</span></span></li>
								<li><span class="icon fa-heart major style2"><span class="label">Ipsum</span></span></li>
								<li><span class="icon solid fa-code major style3"><span class="label">Dolor</span></span></li>
							</ul>
                            -->
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Two -->
  <section id="two" class="wrapper alt style2">
    <section class="spotlight">
      <div class="image">
        <img src="images/departure.png" alt="" />
      </div><div class="content">
        <h2>DAY 1</h2>
        <p>
          Gathering at 10:00 near a train station which is easy to reach. After
          a briefing, we'll start our first day of cycling (40, 60 or 80km). At
          night, we get together to have dinner and share stories, ideas and
          inspiration. Camping in a field in a small village.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="spotlight">
      <div class="image">
        <img src="images/Camping.png" alt="" />
      </div><div class="content">
        <h2>DAY 2</h2>
        <p>
          Start with a healthy breakfast. Choose between a ride of 40, 60 and 80
          km to go to our second destination. We'll enjoy dinner together and
          get to know each other! And yes, we'll sleep in our tents again.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="spotlight">
      <div class="image">
        <img src="images/cycling_velotour.png" alt="" />
      </div><div class="content">
        <h2>DAY 3</h2>
        <p>
          Last breakfast together before a final ride of 40, 60 or 80 km. The
          festival ends at a train station which has many train connections.
          Farewell drink to say goodbye and see you next year!
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>

  <!-- Three -->
  <section id="three" class="wrapper style3 special">
    <div class="inner">
      <header class="major">
        <h2>All you need to know</h2>
        <p>
          Please read this FAQ section thoroughly so that you know what you're
          getting yourself into. If you can't find the answer on your question
          below, please drop us an email at support@welcometomygarden.org.
        </p>
      </header>
      <ul class="features">
        <li class="icon fa-heart">
          <h3>Why this Festival</h3>
          <p>
            Exploring by bicycle makes you feel alive. It's a unique way to
            discover a region. What if you combine this with meeting other
            enthusiasts and have a great time together?<br /><br />The Velotour
            Festival gives you the opportunity to travel by bicycle in Belgium
            and meet new people.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="icon fa-paper-plane">
          <h3>For whom?</h3>
          <p>
            For both curious-minded people who want to discover bicycle touring
            and experienced bicycle travellers to share their passion and
            stories.<br /><br />From solo travelers to families, everyone is
            welcome. If you are travelling with your 5 best friends, we doubt
            you’ll still have time to meet others, so no groups please!
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="icon fa-paper-plane">
          <h3>Equipment</h3>
          <p>
            Come with your own bicycle. Please note that you'll carry your own
            panniers with camping gear (tent, sleeping bag & mattress) and
            repair kit.<br /><br />Yet, not owning equipment shouldn't stop you
            from participating, ask a friend to lend you equipment or leave a
            comment in the registration form so that we can help you.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="icon solid fa-laptop">
          <h3>Participation fee</h3>
          <p>
            140 euro per person (70 euro per kid & free of charge for children
            under 2 years old). The fee includes 2x breakfast, 2x dinner, basic
            facilities, logistics, coordination, insurance & some other small
            costs (overhead). Lunch & drinks are not included.<br /><br />Check
            out <a href="budget.html">the full budget here</a>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="icon solid fa-headphones-alt">
          <h3>Itinerary</h3>
          <p>
            3 days of cycling with 3 options (40, 60 and 80 km). We won't cycle
            together in 1 big group. It's a 3-day event and it's not possible to
            join for only one day. You'll receive more information about the
            itinerary before the event and on the first day during the briefing.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="icon fa-heart">
          <h3>Activities</h3>
          <p>
            In the evening there will be social activities around bicycle
            touring. Please let us know about your suggestions in the
            registration form! Those activities won't be next to the tents, so
            that you can also rest if you want to.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="icon fa-thumbs-up">
          <h3>Organisation</h3>
          <p>
            This is a community event. During the festival all partipants are
            invited to volunteer and give a hand in either the morning or
            evening.<br /><br />Your registration cannot be resold to someone
            else. You can cancel and get a full refund up to one month before
            the festival. You can only change weekends if there is availability
            left.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="icon fa-thumbs-up">
          <h3>Insurance</h3>
          <p>
            There's a liability and physical damage insurance for all volunteers
            and a basic physical damage insurance for all participants. Yet, you
            participate at your own risk and responsibility. You will be asked
            to sign a disclaimer on the first day to waive any liability towards
            the organising volunteers and must respect the highway code.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="icon fa-thumbs-up">
          <h3>Code of conduct</h3>
          <p>
            The goal of the Velotour Festival is to meet new people and get to
            know each other. It's a must to be open towards others and to agree
            with our <a href="code-of-conduct.html">code of conduct</a>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="icon fa-thumbs-up">
          <h3>Languages</h3>
          <p>
            The Velotour Festival is organised à la belge: a good mix of
            English, French, Dutch and German. Whatever language you speak,
            we'll find a way to communicate with one another.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
